description:
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An opportunity has arisen for an enthusiastic, motivated individual to join our dynamic infection prevention team, and build upon the excellent work already achieved within Bradford District Care Foundation Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post will support the provision of an comprehensive infection prevention and control service and provide specialist advice on infection prevention and control practices.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post will support, develop and implement systems to improve the quality of infection prevention and control management, by the delivery of national directives to develop local quality, patient safety and safe systems of working for staff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post supports and works in collaboration with the Infection Prevention Team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will need to be self-motivated and have a flexible approach to work. Demonstrate excellent communication skills and the ability to engage and motivate others. You must also be computer literate and have good organisational skills and be able to demonstrate that you can work individually or as part of a multi-disciplinary team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Informal visits are strongly encouraged.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Samantha Moorehouse&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: Infection Prevention&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Lead Nurse &amp; Manager Email address: samantha.moorehouse@bdct.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number: 07818063978&lt;/p&gt;
